    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-18T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="674"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/6974: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-18T12:00:00+07:00"
                            >August 18, 1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 18—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>501. My 485, August 3, 2 p.m. McHugh has been told by an informant he believes to
                    be well informed and reliable that the bill establishing a commercial credit
                    fund of 10 million pounds was ready for final approval by the British Government
                    just before Parliament adjourned on August 4 but was withheld on representations
                    from the British Ambassador at Tokyo who urged that the inclusion in this amount
                    of a sum of 3 million pounds for use in promoting sales <pb facs="0712" n="708"
                        xml:id="pg_708"/> to China would embarrass the conversations in progress in
                    Tokyo for the settlement of the Tientsin controversy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
